TRADEMARK AND LOGO POLICY
-------------------------

The name "Futon", the Futon logo, and associated visual assets are protected
intellectual property and are NOT covered by the GPLv3 license.

Logo Copyright:
  The Futon logo is jointly owned by Fleey and Caniv.
  Fleey holds exclusive management and licensing rights.

  Permitted (non-commercial, referential use only):
    - Use in blog posts, tutorials, reviews, or educational content
    - Display in community discussions or presentations
    - Include in screenshots or documentation of the OFFICIAL software

  Prohibited without permission:
    - Commercial use (merchandise, paid products, advertising)
    - Modification or creation of derivative logos
    - Bundling in ANY modified version of the software (forks), regardless of
      commercial or non-commercial intent
    - Use in ways that imply official endorsement

  Asset Checksums (for verification):
    branding/official/logo.svg
      SHA-256: 30d554edfdc7eb72e60639dc083bbe258ee923147155a7e59aa54347135f9836

If you distribute a modified version of this software, you MUST:

1. REMOVE all official branding:
   - Remove or replace all official logos (see branding/README.md)
   - This applies regardless of whether your fork is commercial or non-commercial
   - Change the application name (do not use "Futon" or similar names)
   - Update APP_NAME and SERVICE_NAME in daemon/core/branding.h
   - Change the package name if distributing an Android app

2. NOT imply official endorsement:
   - Do not claim your fork is "Futon" or "Official Futon"
   - Do not use the Futon name in a way that confuses users
   - Clearly indicate that your version is a fork/derivative

3. PRESERVE attribution:
   - Keep the original copyright notices in source files
   - Acknowledge the original project in your documentation

This trademark policy follows the model established by Mozilla Firefox
(which Debian renamed to IceWeasel) and Chromium/Chrome.


RATIONALE
---------

This policy exists to:
- Protect users from malicious forks claiming to be official
- Maintain quality standards for the official release
- Allow the community to freely fork while preventing brand confusion

You are FREE to:
- Fork and modify the code for any purpose
- Distribute your modifications
- Use the code commercially
- Create derivative works

You must NOT:
- Use "Futon" branding for unofficial releases
- Imply your fork is endorsed by the original authors
- Distribute malware under the Futon name
- Use the Futon logo without permission


CONTACT
